                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-825">
                        <quote source="#bib825-1">Monk and missionary.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="description">In hagiography: John of Daylam was a monk from the region of Ḥadita who converted many pagans and even travelled to Damascus and Jerusalem, where he met Caliph ʿAbd Al- Malik. He built a monastery for Persian monks in the region of ʿArragan.</note>
